Product name: Stained elevated feeder/ dog bowl stand with 3 bowls
Description:
Reclaimed wood elevated pet feeder with removable dishwasher safe, stainless steel bowls included. All stands are sealed with polyurethane for protection and a smooth finish, unless otherwise requested. 
Each feeder can be kept clean with mild soap, water, & a soft sponge or cloth.
The dimensions of the 3-bowl stands are approximately 29.25" long x 10.75" wide x the height you select to purchase.
We offer our stands in the following standard heights:
6 inches tall
8 inches tall
10 inches tall
12 inches tall
14 inches tall
Stands can be made for taller or shorter upon request. Please message us to determine if we can create a feeder stand for your needs and we will create a separate listing for it as applicable.
BOWL SIZE:
Stainless steel 2 quart bowls are included with feeder (holds approximately 7 cups)
Note: The 2 quart size bowls may be larger than desired if you have a very small dog (e.g. shih tzu, chihuahua, etc.). Please contact us if you'd like a custom size feeder built to fit smaller bowls.
HOW TO SELECT YOUR STAIN COLOR &  PERSONALIZATION:
Please select the color you'd like us to stain it from the Stain Color drop-down menu. 
FREE personalization UPON REQUEST: If you'd like any text on the stand (e.g. your pet's name), please request this in the notes to seller at checkout.  ***If no personalization is requested in the notes to seller at checkout, we will assume the buyer does not want any text on the stand.***  
We can include the personalized text in any font available on a PC, so if you have a preference please specify (e.g. you can be specific like "Arial" or "Impact" font, or just note "cursive" or "print" and we'll select one that looks good for you). The lettering is vinyl. We then coat over the vinyl with polyurethane to make sure the lettering sticks on the stand and remains over time.
HOW TO DETERMINE WHICH HEIGHT STAND TO ORDER FOR YOUR PET:
- Please measure the number of inches from your pet's shoulders to the ground. 
- The bowl stand should be just below chin level so he/she can comfortably eat from the bowl without reaching upwards or drastically bending over. 
- We receive many messages requesting what size bowl stand is typical for X breed of dog. While we are happy to provide this information based on what we've seen our customers order, each individual animal is different even if he/she is the same breed as another, so this info is merely meant to serve as guidance and we still suggest measuring your pet to determine the right fit for him/her individually. As an example, we have 3 pitbulls ourselves and 2 of them eat from 12" tall stands but 1 of them requires a 10" stand because she is shorter than the others.
PRODUCTION TIME & SHIPPING:
It typically takes approximately 10-12 business days from date of purchase for us to build your order and ship it out. If you need your bowl stand in a faster time frame, please send us a message before placing your order so we can advise if we have the ability to meet your requested timing and whether a rush fee would apply. 
RALEIGH NC LOCAL PICK UP:
We can arrange for local delivery or pick up if you are in the Raleigh, NC area. There is no charge to pick up, so please use LOCALDELIV as your promo code for shipping costs to be removed from your total at checkout. Please message us so we can make arrangements. Local delivery may result in a small fee, so please message us before using this code if you would like your item delivered or us to meet you somewhere locally.
OTHER FEEDER OPTIONS:
We also offer the stands with only 1 bowl or 2 bowls instead of 3. Please visit our shop to view the listings for these other variations.

Product name: CLOG WORK BOOTS. Portuguese Genuine Clog Boots. Hand crafted and handnailed farm boots.
Description:
Portuguese traditional clog boots (ankle boots), used by farmers and lumberman to keep the feet safe and dry in wet and dangerous environments.
Same shape and materials as the ancient work boots. (All the boots delivered will be new!)
Coverage: Genuine Cow Leather. Attached to the sole with nails.
Sole: alderwood
Rubber layer under the wooden sole.
These boots are totally  handmade in several stages, by different expert artisans: one undertakes the leather's tanning; another one makes the alderwood soles; and a third one sticks the skin to the sole and applies a rubber layer under the sole.
DISCLAIMER ABOUT SIZES
IF YOU'RE A WOMAN, PLEASE PAY ATTENTION TO THE FOLLOWING TIP:
As these boots were originally designed for men (usually big men, like lumbermen), its shape is large. If you are a woman, we strongly recommend you to select one size less.
